arch:property.oc:show_val: X1 is a bone ring fragment, and F1 a fragment of a different ring. Additionally, bird recorded and pulled for export. Moderate size assemblage with mix of sizes and taxa, but dominated by sheep-size. Fairly even body part distribution with significant representation of ribs and to a lesser extent vertebrae. Many of the toes and tarsals are digested, and a certain amount of other digestion. A little burning and gnawing. Surface condition somewhat variable but generally good. Taxa include sheep/goat, cattle, red deer and pig. Also some bits of coprolite, probably dog as they contain bony bits. Range of ages, including some perinatal. Looks like a small bit of midden. Sample 2 >4mm flotation 100% sorted, only diagnostics recorded, rest as flot frags. Generally similar in character to dry-sieved, but mostly little crumbles. Ca. 15-20% burnt, fair amount of digestion. Diagnostics mostly sheep/goat, with one equid tooth.
